<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">This name is based on the style with a long apophysis.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parandanus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Parandanus paracruciatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paracruciatus">Parandanus paracruciatus</taxonomicName>
in color pattern but differs from this and other species by its very long style apophysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
